{"about_the_game":"Load Shedding<br />\r\n<br />\r\nBad Dudes have taken over the island town of Moderio and stolen all of the power for their base. The Townsfolk have asked their local scientist Shaun Zenn to stop them.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nYou have to restore power to the town.<br />\r\nBuild an electrical network by placing devices in the RED, GREEN, BLUE and YELLOW zones across the island. Connect the devices by clicking and dragging the small plugs to each other to form a wire.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFeatures:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n3rd Person Character<br />\r\n<br />\r\nMenu System<br />\r\n<br />\r\nBattery Pack - A battery that has parameters such as maximum energy for charging and discharging. Looking closer, you can find out how much energy is left, and the time until it is completely charged.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSolar Generator - Implements sun tracking for each panel. If, for example, the solar panel is in the shade, then the generation of energy slows. Sunlight is tested for each of the 18 panels.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWind Generator - Checks the current wind speed and adjusts the charge<br />\r\n<br />\r\nHydro Generator - Checks the current tide speed and adjusts the charge<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPost - Large splitter<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSmall Post - Small splitter<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSwitch - You can separate one electrical line from another<br />\r\n<br />\r\nMonitor - Through this connected device, you can find out all the parameters of the electrical network: The number of connected devices, the number of batteries, the number of generators, the amount of accumulated energy, the amount of energy to discharge, the time until all batteries are completely charged<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPower Bank - All the features of a battery, but can be charged from other batteries<br />\r\n<br />\r\nBackpack Powerpack","background":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2983950/page_bg_generated_v6b.jpg?t=1716447890","background_raw":"https://shar